# llama-apps dashboard — copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in.
#
# The dashboard is a thin UI over the control plane's HTTP API. It never talks to
# Postgres or Docker directly — it only needs to know where YOUR control plane is.
#
# >>> DATABASE CONFIG IS NOT HERE. <<<
# The control plane is the only part that uses a database. Set your Postgres
# (PG_HOST/PG_PORT/PG_DATABASE/PG_USER/PG_PASSWORD) in control-plane/.env —
# copy control-plane/.env.example and follow the README. This file is just the
# dashboard's pointer to the control plane.

# Where the control plane is reachable. For the default local setup (control
# plane running on this machine via `npm run dev`) the default below is correct.
# If your control plane runs on another box, tunnel to its loopback port and
# point this at the local end:
#   ssh -N -L 8787:localhost:8787 user@your-box   ->   CONTROL_PLANE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8787
CONTROL_PLANE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8787
